55:05.769 --> 55:09.637
Arrest him! I want that son of a bitch
arrested for assault.

55:20.701 --> 55:23.370
I promise they won't assault you again.

55:23.745 --> 55:24.908
What?

55:28.667 --> 55:30.292
You saw the whole thing.

55:30.544 --> 55:34.672
I saw you and Bo insult Candace
Pennington and attack her father.

55:38.802 --> 55:40.676
No, that's the way I saw it.

55:41.096 --> 55:42.341
Me, too.

55:42.931 --> 55:45.601
He punched my kid for no reason.

55:46.477 --> 55:48.553
I think there was a reason.

56:07.706 --> 56:09.995
What, the picture of you in my bedroom?

56:10.125 --> 56:12.794
What do you do with it
when you have a sleepover?

56:22.596 --> 56:25.217
-So, what do you think?
-About sleepovers?

56:25.766 --> 56:29.217
No, about me coming up.
See, every news outlet in the country...

56:29.353 --> 56:32.389
is dying for some sort of
inside something on this.

56:32.606 --> 56:33.721
I know.

56:34.399 --> 56:38.065
I thought I could come out with
a cameraman and track the investigation.

56:38.195 --> 56:40.900
An inside look at how you're handling it.

56:41.532 --> 56:44.698
-No.
-We could do a whole series about it.

56:45.744 --> 56:48.282
-No, Jenn.
-I'd stay out of the way.

56:56.797 --> 56:58.077
Hey, Abby.

58:09.870 --> 58:10.985
Hey, Jesse.

58:13.457 --> 58:16.078
Two in the chest, just like the others.

58:16.210 --> 58:19.413
Cold morning.
Might make the time of death a little harder.

58:19.546 --> 58:20.709
Hey, Doc.

58:21.632 --> 58:22.830
Not now.

58:31.308 --> 58:32.968
Jesse, I'm sorry.

59:32.452 --> 59:36.118
Maybe I should just say, "The hell with it, "
and be a drunk.

01:00:28.004 --> 01:00:31.503
I don't see what purpose is served
by locking these children up.

01:00:31.632 --> 01:00:35.582
You think they didn't know it was wrong?
That they couldn't control themselves?

01:00:35.720 --> 01:00:39.219
-Well, they didn't.
-No plea-bargains. They deserve jail time.

01:00:40.850 --> 01:00:43.720
Right now, Candace can't imagine
going to school tomorrow.

01:00:43.853 --> 01:00:47.304
She cannot imagine facing all the kids
that will know...

01:00:47.440 --> 01:00:50.144
she was gang-raped
and photographed naked...

01:00:50.276 --> 01:00:54.985
and the three guys who did it
will be in the same school with her.

01:00:55.698 --> 01:00:57.157
Maybe the same class.

01:00:57.283 --> 01:01:00.319
I may not be a little girl anymore,
but I am a woman.

01:01:00.494 --> 01:01:02.653
And as a woman, I sympathise with her.

01:01:02.788 --> 01:01:05.493
Did the court specify
the community service?

01:01:06.667 --> 01:01:07.698
Not yet.

01:01:12.006 --> 01:01:16.419
Let me have each of them in a cell for
an hour. Let me beat the crap out of them.

01:01:17.595 --> 01:01:19.671
-You're joking?
-l am.

01:01:21.307 --> 01:01:25.305
But why not let them serve their sentence
with the police department?

01:01:25.895 --> 01:01:30.058
You would, of course, take your
supervisory responsibilities seriously.

01:01:30.191 --> 01:01:32.100
I would bust their chops

01:01:37.573 --> 01:01:39.233
I'll see what I can do.

01:01:40.868 --> 01:01:43.786
What about unsolved murders
in the Cleveland area?

01:01:45.623 --> 01:01:48.873
A young girl was shot at a bus stop
in Parma, which is near Cleveland.

01:01:49.001 --> 01:01:51.041
I know where Parma is.

01:01:52.588 --> 01:01:55.126
The only thing that matches this m. o...

01:01:55.257 --> 01:01:58.543
are two killings in Hilton Head, 1999...

01:01:58.678 --> 01:02:01.133
and three in Florida, 2002.

01:02:01.389 --> 01:02:02.883
Where in Florida?

01:02:09.772 --> 01:02:12.524
There's a guy from CNN here.
He wants to speak with you.

01:02:15.111 --> 01:02:16.735
He won't like that.

01:02:17.113 --> 01:02:20.529
There's a press briefing every morning.
Tell him where and when.

01:02:20.658 --> 01:02:21.689
Okay.

01:02:22.451 --> 01:02:24.195
Maybe now we can get a search warrant.

01:02:24.328 --> 01:02:27.199
No judge is gonna give us a search warrant
with what we've got.

01:02:27.331 --> 01:02:28.612
And the weapons won't be there.

01:02:28.749 --> 01:02:31.454
-We can try.
-l don't want them to stop!

01:02:49.645 --> 01:02:51.187
That's good work.

01:02:52.231 --> 01:02:54.520
You may make Detective someday.

01:02:56.610 --> 01:02:58.603
We don't have any detectives.

01:03:00.740 --> 01:03:03.065
Well... if we did.

01:03:23.137 --> 01:03:25.213
I'm sorry about your girlfriend.

01:03:26.515 --> 01:03:29.351
She wasn't my girlfriend. She was my pal.

01:03:31.687 --> 01:03:33.146
No, thank you.

01:03:33.272 --> 01:03:35.561
-You're not drinking?
-l don't drink.

01:03:38.027 --> 01:03:39.486
I did, but I don't.

01:03:49.705 --> 01:03:53.454
The DA went for your plan.
So what are you gonna do?

01:03:55.294 --> 01:03:59.208
I'm gonna take them over to Doc Perkins
and have them sterilised.

01:04:01.050 --> 01:04:04.335
The Marino family wants me
to file charges against you.

01:04:05.680 --> 01:04:08.764
-lt all happened so quickly.
-I'm sure.

01:04:09.976 --> 01:04:12.513
I could tell you're kind of slow to react.

01:04:12.645 --> 01:04:15.848
Bo attacked Candace's dad
who responded in self-defence.

01:04:15.982 --> 01:04:19.979
Then Joe Marino jumped in and Chuck
had to defend himself from both of them.

01:04:33.249 --> 01:04:35.822
I was a prosecutor in a previous life.

01:04:37.044 --> 01:04:38.836
Don't beat yourself up.

01:04:39.296 --> 01:04:42.712
lt's the toughest kind of case:
motiveless, random killing.

01:04:43.259 --> 01:04:46.959
lt seems that serial killers only screw up
when it gets personal.

01:04:52.101 --> 01:04:54.058
So, when do we go to court?

01:04:54.395 --> 01:04:56.968
This one isn't a winner for our side.

01:04:57.398 --> 01:04:59.723
I'll persuade my clients to drop it.

01:05:00.109 --> 01:05:02.398
-And if they won't?
-They'll drop it.

01:05:06.866 --> 01:05:10.946
So, off the record, what really happened
with Bo and his father?

01:05:11.787 --> 01:05:15.785
Pennington smacked the crap out of Bo
and his old man, and I let him.

01:05:16.417 --> 01:05:19.169
-I'm shocked.
-Not that shocked.

01:05:23.716 --> 01:05:25.625
lt'll be our secret.

01:05:26.093 --> 01:05:29.379
Perhaps before we're through,
there'll be several more.

01:05:49.533 --> 01:05:52.321
Ballistics came back on the third victim.

01:05:53.287 --> 01:05:56.288
Same as the first two. Same two guns.

01:05:58.000 --> 01:06:01.085
-Who else knows about this?
-So far, just you and me.

01:06:07.593 --> 01:06:09.301
lt's freezing out here.

01:06:10.012 --> 01:06:12.966
The day I left LAPD,
I drove out to Santa Monica...

01:06:13.099 --> 01:06:15.222
and just looked out at the ocean.

01:06:15.768 --> 01:06:18.804
I lost my wife and my job. lt calmed me.

01:06:21.148 --> 01:06:23.853
-Are you feeling that way now?
-No.

01:06:24.026 --> 01:06:25.307
I'm angry.

01:06:26.529 --> 01:06:28.189
They killed my friend.

01:06:28.322 --> 01:06:31.774
So you think it was intentional,
this killing your friend?

01:06:32.785 --> 01:06:33.816
Yes.

01:06:36.038 --> 01:06:37.616
I know who did this.

01:06:39.625 --> 01:06:42.626
I know who killed Eisley,
the woman in the parking lot...

01:06:42.753 --> 01:06:45.244
The guy in ther alley, and Abby...

01:06:46.632 --> 01:06:48.506
I know who killed them.

01:06:49.885 --> 01:06:51.712
-Do you have a motive?
-No.

01:06:51.887 --> 01:06:53.512
-Witnesses?
-No.

01:06:55.099 --> 01:06:58.016
Hell, I'll warm up a cell right now.

01:07:00.062 --> 01:07:01.556
There's two of them.

01:07:02.565 --> 01:07:05.352
And they're not gonna stop. I won't let them.

01:07:12.116 --> 01:07:15.117
So these two people,
they have an interest in killing people...

01:07:15.244 --> 01:07:17.700
and now they seem to have an interest
in killing you?

01:07:17.830 --> 01:07:19.870
ls this a great country or what?

01:07:20.374 --> 01:07:24.953
Jesse, you might want to be a little careful
with these people.

01:07:27.173 --> 01:07:30.506
-I'm a little careful with everyone.
-The hell you are.

01:07:32.762 --> 01:07:35.513
lt would not be good to take this personally.

01:07:36.515 --> 01:07:39.089
I've been at this thing too long to be wrong.

01:07:39.226 --> 01:07:42.975
I'm not gonna sit around
and wait for someone to find another body.

01:07:54.659 --> 01:07:56.900
You just love to make me nervous.

01:08:04.168 --> 01:08:05.283
Need a ride?

01:08:07.338 --> 01:08:08.915
He's going to see you.

01:08:15.554 --> 01:08:16.752
That sounds good.

01:08:16.889 --> 01:08:19.345
-You know what sounds even better?
-What?

01:08:32.488 --> 01:08:34.362
I think he looks worried.

01:08:37.283 --> 01:08:39.609
Maybe we've been too hard on him.

01:08:40.662 --> 01:08:44.957
Human life is like the flight of that sparrow.

01:09:04.353 --> 01:09:05.764
This is Reggie.

01:09:06.604 --> 01:09:08.479
Thought you might need this.

01:09:12.403 --> 01:09:16.234
-They took a ballistics test?
-Yes, we did. We sent it to Boston.

01:09:16.948 --> 01:09:19.654
Come into the living room.
Brianna doesn't wanna miss you.

01:09:19.785 --> 01:09:21.694
Bri, honey, it's Jesse.

01:09:25.624 --> 01:09:28.460
I assume it's not linked
to a drive-by shooting or anything.

01:09:28.586 --> 01:09:31.124
Actually, the rifle's never been fired.

01:09:31.881 --> 01:09:33.872
So much for plinking vermin.

01:09:34.133 --> 01:09:36.837
-Must have been one of your other . 22s.
-No.

01:09:36.969 --> 01:09:38.843
I have no other guns.

01:09:39.680 --> 01:09:40.877
Jesse Stone.

01:09:41.015 --> 01:09:42.343
-Brianna.
-Hello.

01:09:42.558 --> 01:09:44.930
What a beautiful dog you brought!

01:09:45.060 --> 01:09:47.386
Hello. What a sweet doggie.

01:09:47.520 --> 01:09:49.180
Hello, you little noodle.

01:09:49.314 --> 01:09:52.979
Actually, I've kind of adopted him.
He belonged to the first victim.

01:09:53.109 --> 01:09:55.269
Well, that's awfully good of you.

01:09:56.656 --> 01:09:58.031
How sweet.

01:09:58.991 --> 01:10:01.909
-l think he likes you.
-Of course he likes me.

01:10:05.289 --> 01:10:06.748
You going someplace?

01:10:06.874 --> 01:10:09.709
Well, like we said,
we're only here a short time.

01:10:10.419 --> 01:10:12.661
-When do you leave?
-Tomorrow night.

01:10:13.005 --> 01:10:16.837
-How's the investigation going?
-Actually, not too good.

01:10:17.927 --> 01:10:20.548
I hope the victims didn't suffer too much.

01:10:20.680 --> 01:10:23.680
I wonder what it's like
to know you're gonna die.

01:10:24.392 --> 01:10:27.013
Have you ever been in that position, Jesse?

01:10:27.228 --> 01:10:30.928
I'm just a small-town cop.
Mostly, I give out parking tickets.

01:10:31.774 --> 01:10:34.347
lt must make everything very intense.

01:10:35.403 --> 01:10:39.270
I always wondered what it was like
for the shooter. That must be intense.

01:10:39.407 --> 01:10:42.277
Exercising the ultimate human power.

01:10:42.410 --> 01:10:46.242
-lf he thinks about that kind of stuff.
-Do you think he does?

01:10:46.372 --> 01:10:49.823
I'm just a small-town cop.
Mostly, I give out parking tickets.

01:10:50.793 --> 01:10:54.127
-Do you have any leads?
-l was pinning my hopes on you.

01:10:55.464 --> 01:10:57.124
Everyone needs a hobby.

01:10:58.175 --> 01:11:01.876
Seriously, though,
why would we do such a thing?

01:11:03.139 --> 01:11:04.549
A shared sickness.

01:11:07.226 --> 01:11:09.135
At least we would be sharing.

01:11:16.444 --> 01:11:18.235
Who was the last victim?

01:11:20.406 --> 01:11:21.865
A friend of mine.

01:11:21.991 --> 01:11:25.075
Abby Taylor. I read that in the paper.

01:11:25.328 --> 01:11:28.531
lt must be very hard
when it's someone so close to you.

01:11:29.623 --> 01:11:30.703
I'm sorry.

01:11:32.251 --> 01:11:33.330
So am l.

01:11:39.008 --> 01:11:42.258
Abigail, oh, Abigail
Have you met Abigail?

01:11:43.512 --> 01:11:46.928
The queen of the tattooed ladies

01:11:54.161 --> 01:11:55.571
How is it?

01:11:56.830 --> 01:11:59.321
My mother is kind of sulky.

01:12:01.126 --> 01:12:03.498
-And your father?
-Daddy's great.

01:12:03.670 --> 01:12:06.956
I never saw him fight with anybody before,
for me.

01:12:10.177 --> 01:12:13.131
-You didn't try to stop it.
-He was winning.

01:12:14.598 --> 01:12:16.471
Daddy boxed in college.

01:12:16.767 --> 01:12:20.467
He must have been pretty good.
There's not a mark on his face.

01:12:20.896 --> 01:12:23.683
-Did you ever box?
-l don't box, I fight.

01:12:24.941 --> 01:12:27.017
-What's the difference?
-Rules.

01:12:30.906 --> 01:12:32.945
So, how is it at school?

01:12:35.368 --> 01:12:39.152
Sometimes Bo or Troy will stare at me
when I go past.

01:12:40.165 --> 01:12:41.992
But they don't say anything.

01:12:44.336 --> 01:12:48.749
Everyone else, most of the kids,
have been okay about it.

01:12:50.050 --> 01:12:51.164
Good.

01:13:01.520 --> 01:13:04.474
I want you to know
I appreciate what you did for me.

01:13:06.942 --> 01:13:09.230
-Could you do me a favour?
-Sure.

01:13:09.986 --> 01:13:13.438
Reggie here has got no owner, no family.

01:13:14.866 --> 01:13:16.693
I'm never home...

01:13:17.411 --> 01:13:19.948
and he really needs someone
to look after him.

01:13:20.080 --> 01:13:22.832
-Could you do that?
-l don't know, my mum--

01:13:22.958 --> 01:13:25.200
I can talk to your mum about it.

01:13:26.211 --> 01:13:28.120
But you have to take care of him.

01:13:28.255 --> 01:13:31.421
-Feed him, walk him, clean up after him.
-l know.

01:13:32.717 --> 01:13:34.046
I can do it.

01:13:35.220 --> 01:13:36.714
I know you can.

01:13:48.525 --> 01:13:49.556
What?

01:13:52.112 --> 01:13:53.986
I'm sorry about your friend.

01:13:56.074 --> 01:13:57.616
Thank you, Candace.

01:14:21.308 --> 01:14:24.593
-So, why Abby?
-Because she was close to me.

01:14:26.813 --> 01:14:30.645
-So you think they want to kill you next?
-l kind of wish they'd try.

01:14:32.486 --> 01:14:34.562
I know they're not finished.

01:14:36.615 --> 01:14:40.315
They know where you live. Why don't
they lurk around your house and shoot you?

01:14:40.452 --> 01:14:42.943
They want to do something more artistic.

01:14:43.080 --> 01:14:45.571
They are crazy. I tend to forget that.

01:14:45.874 --> 01:14:47.914
I think they made a mistake.

01:14:49.252 --> 01:14:50.747
lt's not random anymore.

01:14:50.879 --> 01:14:54.213
They seem to want to taunt me,
see my reaction.

01:14:54.883 --> 01:14:57.718
You might want to think
about being a little careful.

01:14:57.844 --> 01:14:59.255
I need evidence.

01:14:59.930 --> 01:15:02.136
You think they'll come at you the same way?

01:15:02.265 --> 01:15:05.219
Serial killers like ritual.
They'll do it the same.

01:15:05.602 --> 01:15:09.979
Jesse, you're a good man and a good cop.
Better than this town deserves.

01:15:11.566 --> 01:15:13.808
lt matters what happens to you.

01:15:14.778 --> 01:15:18.692
The ugly truth of it, Moll,
is it doesn't matter a hell of a lot to me.

01:15:19.741 --> 01:15:22.113
A lot of people love you, Jesse.

01:15:23.036 --> 01:15:25.159
-lncluding you?
-Especially me.

01:15:26.039 --> 01:15:28.530
And don't shut me off by being cute.

01:15:29.418 --> 01:15:31.410
lt's hard for me not to be cute.

01:15:42.681 --> 01:15:46.216
I think Reggie will be good for Candace.
That was sweet.

01:16:32.689 --> 01:16:36.557
I don't know if I thanked you enough
for all that you've done for me.

01:16:37.277 --> 01:16:40.728
I mean, you did so much,
and now maybe Reggie and....

01:16:42.574 --> 01:16:45.908
Well, ljust wanted you to know that
I'm your friend...

01:16:46.036 --> 01:16:49.072
and I feel really close to you.

01:17:08.475 --> 01:17:10.598
-It's Jesse

01:17:11.895 --> 01:17:14.979
Listen, I need to see you
both beofre you leave.

01:17:15.107 --> 01:17:19.603
The parking lot by the canal,
where Abby Taylor was killed. You know.

01:17:20.153 --> 01:17:22.442
-When?
-Tonight, 10. 00.

01:17:22.572 --> 01:17:24.197
ls this official?

01:17:40.674 --> 01:17:43.165
He thinks he's setting some sort of trap.

01:17:43.760 --> 01:17:46.132
-Can he do anything?
-lt doesn't matter.

01:17:47.389 --> 01:17:50.840
This just makes it easier.
Now we know where he'll be.

01:17:59.234 --> 01:18:00.894
Why am I here, again?

01:18:04.781 --> 01:18:06.904
That's lovely and chivalrous of you...

01:18:07.033 --> 01:18:11.078
and I know you do it because you
care about me, but it's still dreaming.

01:18:12.164 --> 01:18:14.702
-You see anything, Sult?
-Nothing yet

01:18:21.923 --> 01:18:23.963
That's why I've got you, Molly.

01:18:42.235 --> 01:18:44.524
Jesse, I don't think they're coming.

01:18:58.585 --> 01:19:01.206
We'll get there as soon as we can.
You got that, Suit?

01:19:01.338 --> 01:19:02.452
On our way.

01:19:32.661 --> 01:19:35.662
-l won't have a dog in my house.
-This is different.

01:19:39.543 --> 01:19:41.998
-I'll take care of him.
-Except for when you don't.

01:19:42.129 --> 01:19:43.208
Dad.

01:19:48.885 --> 01:19:51.459
Margaret, this means so much to her.

01:19:51.805 --> 01:19:55.304
-You know the rule.
-Can't we bend the rule this time?

01:19:55.559 --> 01:19:57.017
Reggie needs a home.

01:19:57.144 --> 01:20:00.098
You know how I feel
about animals in the house.

01:20:00.313 --> 01:20:02.887
He's a great dog. He's already housebroken.

01:20:03.108 --> 01:20:05.777
-I promise, I'll take care of him.
-Margaret.

01:20:06.319 --> 01:20:09.985
-But I really want him.
-l won't have a dog in my house.

01:20:10.323 --> 01:20:13.942
-This is different. I'll take care of him.
-Except for when you don't.

01:20:16.830 --> 01:20:18.454
Candace isn't home.

01:20:55.327 --> 01:20:56.655
Pick it up.

01:21:01.541 --> 01:21:04.328
-And let you execute me?
-Pick it up.

01:21:07.422 --> 01:21:09.214
I didn't shoot anybody.

01:21:11.510 --> 01:21:15.922
I may do some jail time,
but no court of law will execute me.

01:21:19.684 --> 01:21:21.724
I'll outlive you, Jesse.

01:21:30.570 --> 01:21:31.768
Get up.

01:22:35.177 --> 01:22:38.343
Put the gun away, Suit,
before you shoot somebody.

01:22:42.184 --> 01:22:43.594
You all right?

01:22:47.314 --> 01:22:49.105
Two guns, one shooter.

01:22:50.776 --> 01:22:52.400
Give that to Healey.

01:23:59.886 --> 01:24:01.713
What are you looking at?

01:24:05.225 --> 01:24:07.550
Jesse, are you there?

01:24:10.522 --> 01:24:11.897
I'm sorry.

01:24:12.899 --> 01:24:17.360
I want you to know that I realise I was
thinking only about myself and my career.

01:24:17.821 --> 01:24:20.608
And I know
I've often been that way with you.

01:24:23.618 --> 01:24:26.489
Jesse, are you there?

